The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Record investment in Bengal

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 7: Bengal has seen investments worth Rs 3,000 crore flow in during 2006, the highest in the state in a calendar year.

 Commerce and industries secretary Sabyasachi Sen today said 221 industrial projects had been set up in 2006, providing employment to around 35,000 people.

 The investments include Rs 100 crore in the Calcutta Leather Complex, Rs 36 crore in Manikanchan at Salt Lake, Rs 65 crore in a vegetable oil refinery in Budge Budge and Rs 12 crore in Indus Dairy at Bankura. 

 The projects in which the investments were made started functioning in 2006, he added.

 Projections for 2007 indicate that investments will cross Rs 4,000 crore, Sen said.

 The state government is also confident about setting up a chemical hub at Haldia. 




